The paper deals with a combinatorial optimization problem of recovering a hidden Hamiltonian cycle from noisy edge measurements, which is motivated by a problem in genome assembly. The analysis relies on the combinatorial characterization of the extreme points of the fractional 2-factor polytope, and the evaluation of the algorithm on real data shows improvements over existing approaches. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
